MINNA – A 50-year-old man has been arrested by the Niger State Police Command for a raping his two middle age daughters in the  Suleja Local Government Area of the state. The suspect, Peter Ayemoba,  was picked up by the police after a complaint by a relation of his family. Ayemoba was alleged to have started having the canal knowledge of his two daughters for over six years. It was gathered that the victims are between the ages of 20 and 22 and had been having sex with their father since 2013 until he found himself in police net. It was said that the suspect had on several occasions threaten to kill the women and commit suicide if they deny him sex. Ayemoba said, “The last thing my daughters will do is to deny me sex when I want it especially when I am drunk, once the spirit of having sex befalls me  any of them that is available will have sex with me.” The State Police Public Relations Officer, Wasiu Abiodun, confirmed the incident,  saying the suspect confessed to the crime. (Punch) The mother of a 14-year-old schoolgirl who was allegedly abducted by a three-man kidnap syndicate recently, Mrs Ukamaka Onyechi, was terribly alarmed when she got a call from her daughter’s guardian in school decrying her absence several days after school had resumed. At first, the rattled mother found the message… February 23, 2020 In "Metro" A kidnap suspect has made a starling confession after being nabbed for his criminal acts in Niger State. According to The Nation, another suspect has been arrested in connection with the kidnapping of the daughter of one Sariki Aliyu, of Kudun-Gure Fulani settlement camp Kotonkoro in Mariga Local Government Area of… October 23, 2019 In "Metro" A pastor of a Pentecostal church has been arrested for allegedly impregnating a 14 -year- old girl in Lagos, Sun News reports. Also in the police net is a father who allegedly raped his daughter and two of her friends. Another man was also caught pants down allegedly for raping… July 7, 2019 In "Metro"